section.t:
The predicate's matching pattern is expressed as a string 
      value conforming to the JavaScript Regular Expression syntax (see 
      ).

figure.artwork:
PATCH /some-document HTTP/1.1
Host: example.org
Content-Type: application/json-patch-test+json

[
  {
    "op": "matches",
    "path": "/a/b/c",
    "value": "\\d{3}"
  },
  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/a/b/c",
    "value": "ABC"
  }
]

PATCH /some-document HTTP/1.1
Host: example.org
Content-Type: application/json-patch-test+json

[
  {
    "op": "remove",
    "path": "/a/b/0",
    "if": {
      "op": "type",
      "path": "/a/b",
      "value": "array"
    }
  }
]

PATCH /some-document HTTP/1.1
Host: example.org
Content-Type: application/json-patch-test

[
  {
    "op": "remove",
    "path": "/a/b/0",
    "unless": {
      "op": "undefined",
      "path": "/a/b"
    }
  }
]

PATCH /some-document HTTP/1.1
Host: example.org
Content-Type: application/json-patch-test

[
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/a/b",
    "value": [],
    "unless": {
      "op": "and",
      "apply": [
        {"op": "defined"},
        {"op": "type", "value": "array"}
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/a/b/-",
    "value": "ABC"
  }
]
